@murrdpirate I'm seeing the same effect on PyTorch 1.1.0. I'm not sure the reason. I tried playing around a bit before also with no success. 

On the bright side, single GPU speed is the fastest we've seen: 0.20 seconds for 16 images is only incredible <13 ms inference time per image (!), or 80 FPS.

The training may be IO constrained. Currently if there are < 1000 training images they are all loaded into memory at the beginning of training, if not they are loaded as they are needed. So for example if you have 2 GPUs and you want to load (and decompress) 160 images per second, your SSD or hard drive may be the bottleneck.
